      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned i need to set up an escrow account for this house i'm buying in toronto. i'm kinda confused. whats escrow actually and why do i need it for the closing?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow is a neutral third party that holds funds and documents during your home purchase until all conditions are met, like a secure vault managed by a title company or lawyer. In Toronto, this is mandatory for transfers to ensure funds are released only when the legal title changes hands safely. It protects both you and your seller by preventing premature payments or fraud, ensuring the deal closes smoothly and legally.\n\nYou should expect to pay a small monthly fee to maintain this account, which is usually deducted from your closing costs. If you have any questions about the specific amount or timing, ask your realtor to explain the escrow agreement before signing anything.",
